		<div id="comment_body_64881899"><p><div class="quote"><p>This is how the free market works. Stupid people ruined their own business. All the smart people will...go elsewhere and do the same work. The engineers and scientists won't just vanish into smoke. You REALLY want to help secure the future? Incentivize those intelligent people to start their own competing companies so that the failure of any single one doesn't cause you to panic. That is, you know, how it's actually supposed to work.</p></div><p>In point of fact, that's exactly how Intel got its start! The so-called <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traitorous_eight" title="wikipedia.org">Traitorous Eight</a> [wikipedia.org] leaving Shockley Semiconductor was arguably the prime mover for the US tech sector's massive growth and long dominance.</p></div>
	</div>

